Monitoring,11/2/2023,11/2/2023,Apache Active MQ Vulnerability,CVE-2023-46604,10.0,,RCE,yes,yes,yes,Qualys QID,no,"CVE-2023-46604
A Deserialization of Untrusted Data vulnerability exists that, when exploited, allows a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code.
This vulnerability has been reported to be exploited in the wild, and exploit code is not publicly available.
Description
Apache ActiveMQ is vulnerable to Remote Code Execution. The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker with network access to a broker to run arbitrary shell commands by manipulating serialized class types in the OpenWire protocol to cause the broker to instantiate any class on the classpath.

Analysis
To successfully exploit this vulnerability, and attacker would need to sent a specially crafted data using the OpenWire protocol to a vulnerable target.
 
CVSS
CVSS v3.1 Base
10 (Critical)
